text.paragraph:
Treatment beyond 2 consecutive weeks is not recommended and the total dosage should not exceed 50 g per week because of the potential for the drug to suppress the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal (HPA) axis. In a controlled pharmacokinetic study, some subjects experienced reversible suppression of the adrenals following 14 days of clobetasol propionate foam, 0.05% therapy (See 
                        ADVERSE REACTIONS
                     ).
